AGI - The State Police of Verona intervened after reporting an executive of an important economic reality operating in the province of Verona for a possible scam through the internet. The staff of the accounting office of the company was in fact contacted by the Group's CEO and - in the conviction of communicating with the heads of the industrial group - induced to carry out transfers destined to a foreign current account for a total of more than one million euros. It is a scam that is usually perfected also through web profiling activity and analysis of social accounts of executives and employees of the company, with the acquisition of valuable information on dynamics and corporate relationships. The Postal Police, once received the report, activated the international channels of police cooperation through the Bank of Italy's Financial Information Unit and managed to block the transaction and returning the sum of money before the actual transfer to foreign accounts. The timeliness of reporting and the carelessness of specialized operators have played a key role in the successful outcome of the operation. The scam perpetrated to the damages of the company of Scalger falls within the category of the "CEO Frauds", also known as "truffe of the boss" or "truffe of the CEO", among the most dangerous cyber attacks for the enterprises, that can provide not only economical but also reputable damages to the companies and the managers involved.
<br In this scheme, a person who is located in apical position within a corporate organization and has powers of expenditure, is contacted by a fraudster who, dealing with the managing director of the company, and representing the need for an immediate transfer of funds leads him to transfer a substantial sum of money, normally on a foreign account. This kind of scam is very insidious and difficult to recognize, because normally preceded by a careful preparation activity, made of study and in-depth analysis of the target society, activity of "social engineering" that allows criminals to have nominatives and references on the structure, such as to make the situation of urgency predicted credible.
&nbsp;
Against this kind of scam, here are the State Police tips: pay attention to the receipt of emails or phone calls that urgently request payment of a sum of money, on current accounts other than those normally used, even foreign; pay attention to requests for urgent payments, perhaps with procedures other than those normally followed and to carry out with absolute confidentiality; In case you receive suspicious emails or phone calls, contact through a different and secure communication channel within the company organization the person that the scammer tries to impersonate, requesting confirmation of the situation envisaged; to prepare within the corporate organization of the procedures for the accounting staff that allow to find with certainty the need for the transfer of funds.&nbsp;

