AGI -&nbsp;Smart city. Electrical mobility. Circular economy. The cities of the future are closer if seen from the Greentech Global Forum, the annual appointment dedicated to technological innovation promoted by the Lazio Region with the organization of Lazio Innova, Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation, SIMEST (Italian Society of Internationalization Support), SACE (Italian Agency for Export Credit), Agenzia Ita (Italian Trade Agency) and with the support of Intesa Sanpaolo.
&nbsp;
This year the initiative will be held from 16 to 17 September at the Ostiense Gazometer Complex in Rome, during the Rome Future Week, with a busy agenda of meetings between institutional tables, promotional workshops and networking sessions, to offer international actors the opportunity to present and share solutions and projects to deepen and discuss in reserved sessions. The Forum will see the participation of international representatives of development agencies, industrial clusters, companies, investment funds, economic diplomats and Italian executives, will focus on leading technologies for energy transition and applications for smart city green energy, electronic mobility, advanced services for citizens and the circular economy.
&nbsp;
The aim is to develop joint projects between large international players and selected local companies and to promote innovation and technology transfer between SMEs and large companies globally. The two days were presented this morning at the press conference at the headquarters of the Region in the presence of Francesco Rocca, president of the Lazio Region, Roberta Angelilli, vice president of the Lazio Region and Councillor for Economic Development, Trade, Crafts, Industry, Internationalization, Marco Rago, legal adviser of the Minister for Economic and Development diplomacy (MAECI); Francesco Marcolini, president of Lazio Innova: Angelo Camilli, President Unindustria, Francesca Alicata, head of external relations SIMEST.
&nbsp;
"The meeting today represents a moment of sharing knowledge and experiences, but above all an opportunity to create synergies and strategic partnerships," said Angelo Camilli. "As Lazio Innova we are engaged in the realization of this appointment for which we will carry out follow-up actions with the aim to strengthen relationships and consolidate the collaborations started during the forum, through a digital matching platform. And then again with networking initiatives and project sharing. In addition, through the management of the ERDF bands of the Lazio Region, we will foster joint participation in international competitions by regional and foreign companies", said Francesco Marcolini.
